Students practice in working environment where the knowledge and skills acquired during the studies at the university are essential. The problem situations in the working process will be analysed and the applied solving strategies evaluated with the supervisor from the university.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course is for practicing knowledge and skills acquired during the study at the university in working environment outside the university.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After successful completion of the practice the student: 1. have gained practical work experience; 2. is able to work in a team; 3. is able to adapt to the daily work routines; 4. has an overview of a particular company, its operating environment, market potential, career opportunities in this business, as well as company-specific practical aspects of corporate governance; 5. is able to give a report about his activities in the company: problem setup, goals of the training, specific task of the trainee, the results of work; 6. is able to analyze what it is in the university lessons learned from makes practical use to him/her, which has benefited and what would be necessary to modify or customize in the learning process; 7. is able to analyze how the company gained the experience and knowledge has furthered his education in the university; 8. is able to do periodic self-reflection of how the objectives set have been completed and is able to set new goals for the next reflection period.
